		<turn type="student">I like the job interview one</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Great choice! Let’s do a job interview role play. I'll be the interviewer, and you’ll be the candidate. I'll start by asking questions, and you can respond as if you're applying for a job. Ready? Here's the first question:
		Interviewer: "Good morning, and thank you for coming in today. Could you start by telling me a little bit about yourself and your professional background?"</turn>
		<turn type="student">Good morning , of course I can . I'm from Napoli , and I studied languages , such as <DMCC corr="Spanish">spanish</DMCC> , <DMCC corr="English">english</DMCC> and <DMCC corr="Chinese">chinese</DMCC> for five years , and then <DMCC corr="I">i</DMCC> chose to <LSV corr="pursue">follow</LSV> a degree in political sciences . I had many jobs , <DMCC corr="I">i</DMCC> worked at the Aspen <DMCC corr="Center for Physics">center <LWCO corr="for">of</LWCO> physics</DMCC> as a gardener , <DMCC corr="I">i</DMCC> worked as a waiter , and <DMCC corr="I">i</DMCC> had a small online business</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Interviewer: "That's quite an interesting and diverse background! It sounds like you’ve gained a variety of experiences across different fields. How do you think your language skills and your degree in political sciences would benefit you in this position?"</turn>
		<turn type="student">I think they can be useful in <FS corr="many">mano</FS> ways : I can talk to people from many parts of the world , and my degree can help me - and the whole office - understand some events of the world , so that we can talk to people in the right way</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Interviewer: "That makes sense, being able to connect with people globally is definitely valuable. Can you tell me about a time when you faced a challenge at work and how you overcame it?"</turn>
		<turn type="student">Once , I had to hire a coworker from Iran , <GPR corr="who">that</GPR> eventually had his bank account blocked abroad . Speaking to the <DMCC corr="Italian">italian</DMCC> embassy , I was able to make the bank pay for his stay in Italy . I'm not a genius , I just talk to the right people <LSPR corr="at">in</LSPR> the right time</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Interviewer: "That’s impressive! It shows both problem-solving skills and the ability to navigate complex situations. Working under pressure and finding solutions like that is a strong asset. How do you typically handle stress or tight deadlines at work?"</turn>
		<turn type="student">I usually just make the stress slip away</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Interviewer: "That's a healthy approach! Finding ways to manage stress is crucial. Can you elaborate on what techniques you use to let the stress slip away? And how do you ensure that it doesn't affect your work performance?"</turn>
		<turn type="student">I usually Bring a book to work <FS corr="every day">everyday</FS> . During <GA corr="\0">the</GA> <FS corr="lunch">launch</FS> break , <DMCC corr="I">i</DMCC> read it , and it calms me <FS corr="every time">everytime</FS> that I am stressed . Most importantly , I have <FS corr="healthy">healty</FS> sleep <FS corr="rhythms">rhytmhs</FS> .</turn>
		<turn type="chatbot" who="ChatGPT">Interviewer: "That's a great strategy! Reading can be a wonderful way to escape and recharge. Maintaining a healthy sleep schedule is also crucial for staying focused and productive. Finally, why do you want to work with us, and what do you hope to contribute to our team?"</turn>
